[OVERLAY] VimFu — Ctrl-G U — Keep Undo
[SAY] {key:Ctrl-G}{key:U} tells Vim that the next cursor motion should not break the undo sequence. Normally, arrow keys in *insert mode* create undo breaks. This prevents that.
[SAY] Type a short value inside the quoted string, then keep the undo block before moving the cursor.
[KEYS] 'j$i'
[OVERLAY] j$i  inside quotes

